hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
The location is perfect near Gare du Nord
Hôtel is for night life

Room are mix with men's and women
Toilettes no housekeeping All shift

The bar ground floor is good music and expensive alcohol drinks
The breakfast is very poor just very basic
Good atmosphere for youngers to discover each other with cosy equipment I'm réception area

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
The bar staff and security are fantastic. My friend and I got unwanted and aggressive attention in the bar area and it was dealt with immediately. I felt very safe and it is far better protection than I’ve had at any bars/clubs before. Thank you to the lovely bar lady that I spoke to (tall) and the security staff that helped.

Would highly recommend to anyone looking for a cheap place to stay.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Totally useless. Noisy, warm dormitory. Impossible to sleep. Expensive with poor facilities. I was there for one night in April. It looked nice on the pictures but the reality is nothing like it. There are no real lockers for your valuables and the dormitory was busy with people moving in and out and turning on the light in the ceiling all night long. Useless. In addition, there was an American booking site that pretended to be the establishment. Its just that when doing the reservation they added a surcharge which was not visible when they advertised the rate of the room. Only seen in the amount deducted from the credit card. Stay far away from this place if you can.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
I had a terrible experience at St Christopher's in Paris, where the safety and security measures were severely lacking. During my stay, there was a violent incident in my room, and the management did not take any immediate action to address the situation.

Furthermore, the visibly distressed and openly violent individual involved was allowed to use drugs and return to the hostel without any intervention from the staff!

The situation escalated to the point of threatening violence towards everyone in the room, with some of us being able to escape, and others trapped in our bunks.

We had to contact the Paris police ourselves to ensure our safety, which was a traumatizing experience, particularly when a team had to break into the room, with guns and tasers.

Despite the severity of the situation, the management did not make any effort to apologize or improve security measures in the hostel, even after we informed them the security doors and fobs were not functioning properly, allowing anyone to come and go from the building.

I strongly advise anyone considering staying at this hostel to prioritize their safety and choose alternative accommodation.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
St Christopher’s Inn,GdN.Paris.
Located 200 mtrs from the Gare du Nord,is a large fun hostel based on 6 floors.
Reception staff were friendly and v helpful
You can only access rooms by 3pm,checkout 11am
Facilities include,bar,restaurant,laundry,WiFi microwave and kettle.
There is no kitchen but breakfast is served for €6/7.
There is a large sports bar with food on the ground floor
Dorms are good with,usb,elec light etc in ea bunk
The area has a mixture of all you would expect in Paris’s main train station,incl Eurostar-London
Rooms on high floors better for noise
“All in all” a fun+well run intl hostel
PC

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Stayed here leading sixth form school trip. Excellent location only a few minutes from Gare du Nord. Rooms really clean and staff helpful. Belushi’s Bar on ground floor really good atmosphere, but consequently very loud until 12/1 ish. Most of our group were unable to get any sleep until the music stopped so bear this in mind if booking.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: AWFUL DOES NOT EVEN COVER IT. We arrived and checked into our room and immediately noticed a huge blood splatter on the bathroom wall, and blood on the bed frame. We went to reception and reported the issue, we did not receive an apology but were offered another room. When we went back to the original (blood splattered) room to collect our bags, a cleaner was in the room and she wiped the blood with a DRY towel, no cleaning spray or antibacterial anything. We went to our replacement room to find dried vomit on the toilet seat and a hair which looked extremely pubic on the top bunk bed. We checked out of the hostel 2 hours after arriving for fear of catching diseases - we again did not receive an apology or an offer of a refund from the front desk. Apologies if the attached photos make anyone sick - avoid this hostel at ALL COSTS

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
I have booked for night for £27 but they added all of thing that cost me £98.
the staff behaviour is so rude. it was worst experience I have ever. I cancel the booking my money was not refunded at the same time i booked another hotel cheaper, good service.
I strongly recommend to not book this one

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
When we checked in on a Friday night, the receptionist told us that our room was on the 2nd floor and handed us 4 sets of ear plugs with our keys. Turns out our room faces a courtyard that is part of the bar downstairs. When we got to the room, we understood the need for the ear plugs. The noise/music was bad/loud enough when the 2 person band was playing but got even worse after the band left and the bar only played music. Ear plugs do nothing for the pounding bass from the music, and the bar plays music until 2AM. If you're going to put us in this crappy room at least adjust the rates you charge for it. The room itself was okay except for the large hole in the floor that was covered by the vinyl planking.
The only good things about our stay were the nice staff at the front desk, the comfortable bed and the proximity to the Gare Du Nord train station.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
Horrible don’t come here. Beds didn’t have bedding when my friend and I arrived. We asked for replacements twice and still nothing, waited 2 hours while both exhausted and just wanting to sleep. The lady on reception was very rude back to me when I asked for a later check-out (because we hadn’t be able to sleep), and wouldn’t give it to us.

Was such an awful experience, don’t come here.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Do not book this hostel!!! The room is cold as a fridge because there is no heating!!! It looks more like an overpriced prison dump with security than a hostel. If there is no heating in Paris until the end of November, then the price should be moderate. There are only 4 showers on the whole floor with "hundred" people staying. There is security in front of the hostel asking you for your card, then you have to check in 4 x times in order to get to your room: in front of the elevator, in the elevator, in the corridor when you leave the elevator, and then to get into the room. The elevator is so dysfunctional because you can use one card for one floor, so a bunch of people are all straggling to press the button with each card. On the 3. floor for safety reasons you cannot open the windows - they are locked, so there is some kind of strange ventilation mechanism that starts buzzing from early in the morning until late in the evening and you cannot switch it on nor off. It made the room even colder. About the location: the area around Gare du Nord is one of the most dangerous locations to go for a walk in the evening in Paris. Yeah, it is well-connected, but it is not a place where you can go for a walk in the evening. Because of the club downstairs, in some rooms, it is super noisy. I want to thank to cleaning staff and people working at the reception. They were super nice and were working really hard.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: The staff were so lovely and helpful! I needed to print off some visas and they happily helped. The rooms and the bed were very comfortable. It was a great way to kick off my travels! Would definitely stay again!!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
No one expecting for even a good service from this hostel stuff but no need to be rude and highbrow to the customers .
very good going with each other but Stuff is rude . Rooms are clean. Showers and toilets are rubish can't estimate when they were last cleaned. I stayed for 5 nights ,last they they asked me to leave the lobby telling they can not let me wait at the lobby . It was just a seat i was occupying.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
Had a really good stay there! I went with one friend and we met amazing people! The bar is cheap and nice!! A perfect way to meet new friends from around and from the hostle.
I recommend.
Our windows was broken and they fixed it! It’s not Wow but it’s still cute!
The bathroom is really basic.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
I stayed in a shared bedroom with 10 beds for 4 nights and it was far from what the pictures promised.
The hygiene there was far from okay and the showers were to badly cleaned I think there were mould there. Same goes for the toilets and sinks because they were not properly cleaned. The bed set was not okay either and the second night I discovered stain marks on the duvet.

You had barely to none reception, there were no chance of good wifi. And my key card didn’t work properly because I had to try again almost every time I had to use it other wise it would not be recognised.

However they had a private “dining area” or a room only visitors of the hostel could have access to and that was pretty nice.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: at an awful awful experience. I don’t even know where to begin! Let’s start with the bartenders at Belushi’s, i know your job is really hard serving overpriced drinks to happy tourists but the attitude is really unnecessary. Secondly our dorm. We’ve slept in many a hostel and never had such a bad experience. The elderly gentleman in the corner spent all night moaning in his sleep as well as coughing up a lung. The couple who woke up at 4 am to unpack and repack their entire luggage for an hour and not pay any mind to the other guests. The boogers on the wall next to your face. The endless amount of mosquitos. The people who just walk in and leave the lights on at 2 am. The man coughing up a lung in the common dining area too! Everyone seemed sick and under the weather and it was just disgusting g. No one here has any common decency for their room mates, the common decency you’ll find at most any hostel across the world. I cannot tell you enough how bad this place was. Never stay here.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
I went there while I saw they had availability on the website, she did check ins in front of me (she didn’t have sense of custumer service with them neither). So she refused to book a room for me, I did not have a place to stay as my nights in Disneyland finished, my flight was unexpectedly delayed and this girl did not even try to listen.

Where is the quality of her reception skills?

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Look, the location is nice because it's right by the gare du nord station and that's the extent of the positives for me. When we checked in, they informed us we would be receiving free breakfast in exchange for a positive review, well jokes on you because you're not getting one, I will not be bribed! I don't like when a company offers you something for free so you can give a good review. You bet I ate free breakfast though. However, I was in Paris, I should have been having an actual good meal so whatever, at least I saved money. Anyways, onto the hostel. Here's the thing, the hostel surrounds a restaurant/bar/club. This is good when you want to eat at the hostel, this is bad when it's 2 AM on the weekend and you want to sleep but can't because the music is blasting and the bass is thumping in your chest. I couldn't believe someone designed a space where people are supposed to sleep directly above a loud club. If it was next door I would have understood, but no, it is attached to the hostel. I also came back at around 7 pm the next day thinking I could rest a bit, but nope, the music was there then too. The other thing I hated was the flooded bathrooms. I take a shower and the drain is clogged so the water starts flooding into the bathroom itself. You go into a stall and there's a puddle of water by your feet, how did that even get there? And it happened in both bathrooms near my room. They have floor squeegees in the bathroom. The room itself was fine. Had curtains in the bunks and a sink plus a table but the flooded bathrooms and loud music on the weekends all night made me dislike my stay. I will say the staff was very nice and they did have events for guests but you're still getting a negative review. Thanks for the free breakfast though!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
On check in the staff were very friendly, BUT, the morning staff were very rude to me and my friends when they came to meet me. She rolled her eyes at the simplest of questions regarding the lockers for their bags.
In addition to this, the security is supposed to be there to ensure safety, but was again very rude, and intimidating, bearing over four young women, and kept staring at me and my friends, making us feel incredibly uncomfortable!
We had intended to all stay there another night but because of the above reasons we decided to go elsewhere!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Stayed here for two nights and had a great experience. Rooms and bathrooms were clean and comfortable, the bar next door is both cozy and lively, and Enrique at the front desk helped me resolve all of my questions with patience and kindness. Will be coming back when I’m in Paris.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Barry held an amazing mojito making class! We learned a lot and made friends! I love this hostel it is so much fun! Its my first night here and I already made a bunch of friends! I stayed at st Christopher’s in Berlin and it was amazing too. I recommend this hostel and the bar Belushi.. most importantly Barry’s mojitos every Friday!’n

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Barry taught us how to make amazing mojitos and it was a fabulous experience! It’s super cool they offer free classes. Love the hostel, very good rooms, vibes, and nice people. It seems like a good location too.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Such a good stay for young backpackers! Lively bar and cool night activities. Including the mojito making class with BARRY the absolute legend!! So easy to meet people and they were able to provide such good recommendations for Paris!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Barry taught a fantastic Mojito class that I would recommend to anyone traveling to Paris. Friday’s at St Christopher’s, show up for a good time and for good drinks. Great way to start off any trip, so go!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: The worker Barry - was so friendly and made us feel very welcome. Everyone was chatty and made us feel safe. I will be returning as I loved the atmosphere and the hostel was very clean and lots of activities to do in the evening

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Good bar and lounge areas,Elaine house manager on reception was excellent.The bathrooms need a make over shabby and untidy the dorms just about ok.Very little noise at night considering hundreds of guests staying.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Great hostel. Staff are friendly and rooms are clean and spacious. The curtains across the beds are a great idea for privacy and to get sleep lockers under beds. My only complaint was therevwas no soap on communal toilets. I asked them to put some in-they did once but didn't bother other days

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Overall OK experience. In a great place close to everything and rooms were clean and comfortable. However, the showers were small and always dirty. There was a sort of yellow slime that lingered on the shower floor (I checked each one). This was unpleasant and really brings down my review. The bar was good with a nice atmosphere and the staff were friendly. I really enjoyed my trip but I don't think I will stay here again.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
When I looked into booking a 3-night stay in Paris, I was already familiar with many hostels across Europe. However, I didn't manage to stay in St. Christopher's hostel until my Parisian visit. I didn't know anyone who stayed there in the past to advise, So I booked my place based on online reviews.

Unfortunately, I'm taking the time to write a detailed review, so other people that plan to stay at St Christopher's Gare du Nord would have the entire picture, before investing their time and money by booking a room or a bed there.

Despite the fact that the hostel offer quite cheap offer relatively hotels in the area, I think that at the end of the day the final package that you get doesn't work the discount in price. For example, my experience in Jo&Joe (also a Parisian hostel) was significantly better, and the difference in price was 2-3 euros a night.
St. Christopher's provides a defective product

Problems:

the rooms:
the rooms were not clean. After going back from the shower to the room, I kept having the feeling I need to take a shower again. The curtains of the bed looked like there were not being cleaned for at least six months.
When it comes to power sockets, I stayed in a 4 beds room, and there were barely 2 sockets for all of us in the entire room. Why would you save money on something basic like that?
There was a lack of basic things that really impacted the convenience - another example is the lack of personal lamps, a basic thing you should have when sharing a room with other people. I had to use my camera's flashlight every time in order to not wake up my roommates.

Breakfast: Despite investing a lot in marketing their breakfast, the one that I received in St. Christopher's was the worst I have had, out of all of my trips around the world. As someone who served in the military and used to eat low-quality food, trust me that I'm not exaggerating. There was a very hard baguette, Pastrami, the most simple cheese, yogurt in a huge bowl and fruit salad. that's it. there wasn't even water (!) or cups for coffee. Had to drink coffee from a beer cup...

Showers: I think it's mind-boggling to have 2 showers and 2 toilets in a floor that hosts tens of people, not only that every time I had to go to the bathroom and shower there was usually a line there, but also then all of the facilities become very dirty in a very short period of time. And, they were not being cleaned frequently enough.

To summarize, for me it was a bad experience. There are many other great hostels in Paris and in general that are delivering a great experience at an affordable price, but St Christopher's Gare du Nord fails to deliver the most basic things that travelers need.

Therefore, I recommend staying away from St Christopher's, and finding an alternative for your stay in Paris.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Very dirty place. I slept in a large room with bunk beds. On the wall in my bed the wall was filled with dry buggers. In the shared bathroom there was a sanitary pad hanging on the wall, it had been used. It was definitly one of the filthiest places i have stayed. Glad i spent my time out in the city.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
The receptionist was so slow. She was Spanish and she took a million hours to make the check in !! That was the first time someone took a long time for that. I ve already booked online and there was nothing to do than check my identity but she was struggling and talking to her colleagues while letting me waiting ! That's not great for welcoming.
In their bar also, the security did not let me work inside !! and barmen and barwomen are not that dynamic and welcoming

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
I reserved 2 nights directly on their website, then I cancelled one night few days befores arrival.
Front desk told me it the refund would be slow (around 14 days), but It has been more than one month and I did not get my money back!
I call them many times, nobody picks up the phone.
I wrote them an email, nobody replyed to me.
Very bad customer service!

Rservation STC-GDN-21089477 in case a manager sees this.

Besides this problem, the cleaning was great and the bed was comfortable, we would totally come back if they solve our refund issue.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Hello, It was my first time in Paris, and I’ve booked at St. Christopher’s Hostel. Barry at Belushis bar taught a great mojito class on Friday. I would definitely come back to and recommend it to a friend.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Went here for a weekend and felt very welcome. Right away our bartender Barry offered us a free mojito making class and gave us great advice on what to do in the city. Fantastic service! 5/5 service!!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: The bar is the center of social culture here. Stayed for a week and my favorite activity was by far Barry’s make your own mojito class. Not only learned a bunch from a fun social teacher, got free drinks and met 20+ new friends from all over the globe. BUT SERIOUSLY IF YOU GO THERE ASK FOR BARRY, HE IS THE BEST BARTENDER THERE AND PROBABLY IN PARIS!!!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Awesome mojito making class with Barry. Easy directions and super fun class with other travellers. Barry ensured we half all the tools and ingredients necessary. Highly recommend when you visit the hostel. Such a fun night!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
I want to state that this is a great hostel. Clean washrooms and beds; comfortable beds, and excellent internet!

Additionally, I want to thank Pelin and the Italian Concierge who checked me in (whose name I didn't get), but he was clearly working the tonight shift and had long hair.

Thanks very much for an excellent stay for first time guest!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I like the fact that every bunk has a curtain because it gives you more privacy and of course it also help protecting you from covid. It is very affordable and the bar has good selections of burgers and chicken wings. The location is dope as it is right by Gare du Nord, that has a direct line to the airport, other major cities in France, other countries and of course the metro line 4. I like staying here whenever I am in Paris.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I know the location of this hostel can be quite scary but it is not. Just look after your stuff and you'll be fine. The hostel beds are so nice and you have your own curtain in your bunk so you'll have more privacy. The location is right next to Gare du nord train station and it also has a direct metro to CDG airport.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: When we made a reservation and went to the hotel, they said that it was impossible for us to pay cash, and that was the procedure. Another customer who was there asked to pay to help us, and we were going to give him cash. But the woman at the reception said very harshly that such a thing was not possible. It was our last day in Paris or even in France. We were in a panic and they were never helpful. They were very rude. They took cash payment for the two people who came after us but they told us it was impossible. The rudest owner people I have ever seen, I am so unhappy that they made our last night so bad. I will never step foot in here again.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I’ve been in hostels and dormitories around the world for more then 20 years. I would not go back to this place. It is huge and the reception seems to take it as an argument for the bathrooms to be uncleaned. Showers and toilets were not clean. Corridors have no end and you have to pass multiple doors from the elevator to finally get to your room. I felt like I was sleeping in a warehouse. There was no air con and some people had problems with their windows that would not open. Good to mention that gare du Nord is a crappy neighborhood.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I have only had the pleasure of spending one night at the St Christopher’s Inn but i have had so much fun and made so many friends. If you are looking for Parisian nightlife, this is the place to go. We were given a free workshop on making mojitos by Barry it was so awesome. I would recommend this hostel to any students traveling on a budget looking to have some fun.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Amazing staff and customer service. The trip was amazing the customer service was amazing. You are greeted at reception by lovely staff and the atmosphere as amazing . 5 star would defo about visit again

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Parry the Irish was great! He taught us how to make mojitos and made us feel very welcome here! We met lots of people from around the world and there was just a really great vibe inside the bar with all the other travelers. We hope to go to St.Christopher’s inn in other countries

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Well located hostel, close to subway and train station. Clean private room, great for two people. They lend a hair dryer and iron if the guest needs it. The staff is attentive and my stay was very peaceful. I recommend!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I stayed at st Christopher’s for a weekend and I had an incredible experience solely because of Barry the bartender! He was so nice and welcoming. He made my friend and I feel so welcomed and comfortable in the hostel. Go to st Christopher’s just to meet this amazing bartender!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I loved all of the social events, especially the wine and cheese evening was a success! Barry was very nice and welcoming, he‘s the best bartender I‘ve met in a hostel! Highly recommend coming here. If you come to the bar, order the fries, they are very yummy.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Awesome hostel. Bar is great. Bartender Barry was mad cool. Great location, clean, good security and near 2 mero stations. Lots of partying yet quiet in the rooms. Perfect for solo travelers and others alike.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: We really enjoyed our recent stay at st Christopher’s inn, the hostel was perfect for our needs and located close to the train station. One of the highlights of our stay in Paris was an evening spent in the adjoining bar, where our fellow Irishman Barry made sure the drink was flowing and everyone was in good form, I would definitely recommend this hostel and bar 🇮🇪

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Such a good vibe at the hostel. A perfect place to meet new people and socialise - easy when bartender Barry is on the job making sure everyone is having fun and never an empty glass! I can only recommend this place to all travelling by yourself or with a friend.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
Wonderful hostel, everything’s clean and the people are so nice. Even in a 10 bed room very good to stay there :) Especially the barkeeper Barry made us feel welcome and made sure everyone was socializing well.
Also the train station is 2 minutes away which was very good. When I’ll go to Paris next time I know where I’m gonna stay!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
Beautiful hostel with nice people and a cool atmosphere!
Barry made the cheese and wine night a very pleasant experience🌌. I would definitely recommend staying here if you want to visit the city Paris!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
The hostel was so nice! A beautiful location with a lot of stores and restaurants. They organize a lot of fun things to do so you can meet a lot otlf other tourists and have fun. The service was so great!! Especially from Barry :))

Barry is amazing

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
An amazing hostel with a nice program every night. This night there was a really great wine and an amazing cheese pallet, served by the amazing Barry <333

Barry is truely great, he is so nice. I’m just typing this because I have to fill the 200 characters :) but he rlly is great

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Barry is the best bartender ever! And the hostel is nice, everything is clean and the beds are nice. The only thing is that you have to bring your own padlock to lock your suitcase, so remember to bring that! Didn't get to try the food. Just go here!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Barry made my night can’t recommend enough. I can’t get into specifics even though trip advisor requires 200 character (which is annoying by the way). I as an Irish American from New York I was honored to meet a real Irish person in the beautiful city of Paris

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
When arriving to the area, it felt a little dangerous. However the hostel is 2min away from gare du nord so it was easy to find.

regarding the hospitality - AMAZING.
The receptionist were so helpful and gave us all the information we needed

As for Mr. Barry😂 best bartender ever. Gave us good recommendations and also made our last nights at the St. Christopher’s Inn super fun.

Thank you so much St. Christopher’s Inn for this experience.

Lois.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: BARRY IS THE BEST BARTENDER IN PARIS!!!! Cheers! Great bar!!! The food was amazing, drinks have good prices and they atmosphere is always great. Music is good and you always meet new and nice people!! Come to belushis gare du nord asap!! 👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
I usually like hostels as they are more affordable and social compared to hotels. A tradeoff in comfort is part of the deal.

Unfortunately this hostel was not for me. The signiture bar/nightclub of St Christopher's Inn is located at the hart of the hostel, giving al rooms with a courtyard view entertainmant throuought the night. Good if you like to party the night away, but not if you just want a decent night's sleep.

Additionally, I was grossed out by my pillows. Even though they had clean cassings, the verry sharp sweat odor was unbearable.

Not my best hostel experience.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: We had the absolute pleasure of being served by an incredible Irish bartender by the name of Barry. He was great for recommending drinks and had a great spirit. Made my holiday in Paris. Great craic altogether!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Great atmosphere in the bar, fantastic staff - was lucky to be served by the excellent Barry on our first night in the bar. He made our night! Staff were very accommodating checking in and the hostel is very clean and in a great location!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: The hostel is super fun, they organize different activities for you to get to know other people. Also, the staff is incredibly friendly and create a great atmosphere; especially Barry! He made our stay even more enjoyable with his kindness and hospitality :)

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
Good food, good location, special regards to my friend Barry the barman. Very very nice
100% recommended.

Nevertheless, tripadvisor obliges me to write 200 words as minimum, wich is bloody ridiculous.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Private room is extremely satisfactory, great location in the city with ease of access to all amenities. Coming from the UK we find it hard to communicate in French but the bartender Barry gave us many suggestions on the local area, and made our stay at the bar a great night! Hats off to him for great service!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: We weren’t too sure about the area or place but Barry the bar man made us feel right at home and showed us the best locations. I would definitely return to this place because of Barry and because it was very good! Would highly recommend

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Barry made some bomb crepes for us and was a great host for our event. The irishman was super social and hospitable, giving us travel and hostel information and just being an over welcoming and kind worker. Would recommend.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: A particular mention to Barry who works here, i fell and hurt my knee and he was beyond helpful, he made my experience at the hotel beyond excellent and I couldn’t have asked for better help, even after that when I saw him in the bar he continuously asked me how my knee was and made sure I was ok, he brought my drinks to me because he knew I was hurt and couldn’t walk properly, I could not recommend this hostel enough and be sure to ask for Barry because he will show you an amazing time!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Great bar for solo travellers, the barman Barry introduced me to a group of other hostel goes immediately on arrival. This and the generally lovely atmosphere makes this a perfect spot for solo travellers. Great live music was played and the food is good too!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Barry was amazing on mojito night , and he truly made our night special. He treated us as friends instead of just as clients. The bed accommodations were also great. My friends and I were comfortable the whole stay. Big up Barry!!!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Great hostel and a lot of fun. The bar was a lot of fun too. One night there was a free mojito promotion and we were taught how to make mojitos. The bartender Barry showed us how and made it fun. Afterwards we taught the next group, and it made for a great environment.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Good staff, excellent location. One negative point is the toilet. Few box for large floor w/ uncountable bedrooms. Next to gare du nord. 5 minutes walking or less. Didn’t find any supermarket next to.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I have booked and payed i did pay more of the original price paid i would not recommend it to others sorry in the morning at the check out desk the lady who was working there she a very bad attitude and she tried to charge me more of what I paid it meant to coast me 35£ it did coast 70£

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Me and my friend stayed for 3 nights and it was wonderful. Excellent service and maintenance of rooms. We were told complimentary breakfast would be provided but they said it wasn't when we arrived there because of covid which is understandable but they could've given us a heads up. But it overall the stay was excellent.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: The desk is always open, and the staff is practical and friendly. They are always willing to help everyone. Most of the rooms are clean. The place is well located. The bathrooms could be cleaner, but its ok.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Yea was great.. first night was a bit confusing as I had to stay at another hotel as there wasnt any space when I got to the hotel...never mind as the next evening I signed in -€50 ....lol next time ill just stay at the Paris Hilton!! Really great actually... nice and quiet or with a busy city right on the doorstep

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
A very nice hotel, excellent service and very nice staff. My tourism will be coming also in the same hotel. I will invite my friends from Germany to visit this respectable hotel
Thank you for this room service number 518

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: my trip was excellent thanks for the hospitality giving to me by St Christopher's saft I enjoy my stay there very nice location in Central of Paris everything is close super market train station metro station I enjoy my stay there thanks for the saft.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
The staff is friendly. The premises are clean and tidy.
Free WiFi ! Hot showers and air conditioning in the rooms in the summer ! Belushi’s is the place to go-go for drinks, snacks, music and fun ! The best youth hostel in Paris !

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
In response to COVID-19, these additional safety and sanitation measures have NOT BEEN RESPECTED to this property.

" Reduced Capacity Dorms " as stated by their booking webpage : I can confirm the dorm i am staying in have people both on top and bottom beds with 90% occupancy. Plus the air conditionning is not working very well over the whole bulding rooms.

Plus, as mentionned on the major booking websites, no remorse on puting you in first floor constant with traffic noise. No, the "this is a party hostel" excuse is not valid as we are on weekdays and the noise is from the streets.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: The rooms were not well maintained and there was very less security. I got stolen by people from outside who entered the room with fake keys and the reception was helpless,what they could do only was checking the security cameras.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
COVID WARNING !
The arabic manager and some latin staff tend to allocate people of colour, regardless of attitude, in the same rooms than economically deprivated people, sometimes with doubtful hygiene and without respecting the allocation of bunkbeds with reasonable distance.
The french managers are much more inclusive and dont base their decision on skin colour only.

Be careful if you care not catching covid positive.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Very affordable hotel, clean, and very nice staff, Close to train station and center of Paris, restaurant and bar with good food, shared microwave and fridge, no air conditioning but there’s a fan if you need.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
Fully satisfied with the stay, having a single room - clean, ideal for a single traveller. Though the closet&shower place was truly tiny (reminding me of our local CZ trains), for a single low-cost person it is enough, escepcially with the bed, where even two people could stay overnight.
The location by the Paris Nord station could not be better, for a late arrival or early leaving the best choice.
Accompanied by a bar with cuisine, I enjoyed my stay. It is worth it!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I was booked in a 8-bed room for a good price, and got an update to a 4-bed room (don't know why). Clean, comfortable, own bathroom. The people at the reception have been very freindly, what can I say? I am very content.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I stayed here for almost a week and liked it a lot. Not situated in the nicest or most welcoming area in Paris, but the hostel itself is very safe, clean and well organised. Staff are very helpful and the bar is a nice place to meet people. Great stay overall, would recommend!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Arrived and got a lovely friendly welcome from the receptionist (didn't get her name but she's from Mexico). The receptionists continued to be incredibly helpful (night manager from Bulgaria explained the best way to get to Beauvais airport and I'm not sure I'd have made it without her!). Hostel was huge but still really secure and hygienic, which was impressive. I could meet lots of people but there was also space if you just want to be quiet and alone. Was also happy with how much locker space was available. Only complaint was that the room I was sleeping had very weak air conditioning, so it was a bit difficult to sleep in the middle of summer, but it didn't ruin my stay.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Nice, clean and most important; quiet hostel! It surpriced me how quiet it was. The location is so central and you hear nothing! Also they had arco's in the rooms. That was really nice, outside it was 38 degrees ;) in the room a lot colder!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: It was a really good place, everything was clean, and the rooms are really nice, the staff was really cool and helpful, people in the hostel are very interesting and nice, next time I'll be in Paris I'll turn back

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I like everything. Pretty clean. Very close to metro. The bar downstairs...The receptionist is very nice she provides me information about the city. Due to viruse there is no breakfast now. But there are a lot cheaper cafe around the hostel. So I like it, it was beautiful.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
That was my second time in St Cristopher’s. For a solo traveler with no special demands to stay a couple of nights in a safe, comfortable place I can surely recommend it.
Bathrooms with showers and toilets are clean and simple. The only thing is that they have no soap to wash the hands.
The rooms are very well equipped, you can have your private space with the personal curtains, you have the place to charge your electronic devices just above your head and personal lights... so I really appreciated the way everything is arranged there, you also have a space for your luggage. Actually among all the commun rooms in all the hostels that I’ve tried in different cities and countries this one is one the best ones.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Excellent front desk service and cleaning crew. Good location too, near Gare du Nord. The toilet/shower areas were well maintained and they were cleaned every few hours. You walk in and know the countertops and toilets are clean. The hostel should have a policy about guests doing and hanging their laundry in the shared room. I didn't have a considerate roommate and she hung her hand-washed laundry all over the room, and she was also loud when talking over the phone using a lot of expletives/vulgarities. Other than that, my stay was quite pleasant.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews:
Nice bunkbeds with curtains. Very clean and cozy. The price was also reasonable. The location is excellent as it is just next to the railway station. Then I gelt like home as the guy at the reception turned out to be Croatian and I am Slovenian :)
If I ever travel to Paris again, I will defenitely choose this hostel again.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: The hostel provides good facilities to the guests. It is one hour by walking from the Eyfeel and Arc de Triomphe. I liked the hostel. But I could not make so much friends there. Generally talking, its price is a bit much comparing its facilities.

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: The staff is very helpfull and open for solutions. Everything was taken care of. The restaurant is very nice, you can have all kind of baverages here and eat a nice meal. Make sure to visit this hostel if you like to be at your place !

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Terrible location, at night I suffered severals harassments on the street of the hostel. the bathroom stank of pee and I was disgusted to take a bath in my bare feet. Also, the bathroom was too small to take a shower!

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Taking out the noise ( normal in the zone of Gare du Nord ) the stay was correct . I took avantage that the hostel is not very full due to the coronavirus . The pub downstairs the hostel is great for a drink in the evening .

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: Super clean facilities, lovely food and selection of drink in the bar! Staff all super friendly & Barry was especially accommodating! Recommend if you’re looking for something affordable and a short walk to Sacré-Cœur / Moulin rouge. Plenty of metros in the local vicinity alongside the main station Gare Du Nord!!🌸

hotel: St Christopher's Gare du Nord Paris
reviews: I would overall recommend my stay at St. Christopher's in Paris. The location is pretty good, right next to the Gare du Nord station that made getting to other parts of the city quick and easy. Belushi's bar and restaurant downstairs was super cool, it had all of the food and drinks a young American could want and an ideal party atmosphere. The only downsides to my stay were the dorms, which were more crowded than I would have liked, and the outside noise which did not cease until very late into the morning (I had a flight the next day). Overall I had a positive experience at St. Christophers and I highly recommend it to other young travelers looking for a fun and affordable place to stay in Paris.
